# T14-tv — laptop lid OPEN + TV over HDMI
# autorandr matches profiles by EDID (the 'setup' file), so this profile
# must be saved on the target machine with the screen physically connected.
# It cannot be fabricated. autorandr ignores this file (only 'config', 'setup',
# and hook scripts matter), so it is safe here as a reminder.
#
# Layout: TV primary, extended left of the laptop panel.
# For mirroring instead of extend, use: --output HDMI-1 --same-as eDP-1
#
# 1. Connect the screen, set the layout:
#      xrandr --output HDMI-1 --primary --auto --left-of eDP-1 --output eDP-1 --auto
#
# 2. Save (writes real 'config' + 'setup' here):
#      autorandr --save T14-tv
#
# 3. Copy back into the repo (live dir is a throwaway stow copy):
#      cp -r ~/.config/autorandr/T14-tv ~/environment/dotfiles/config/.config/autorandr/
#
# 4. Commit.
